HEADWORD: Hosteler
<hw>Hos"tel*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Hostel</er>, and cf. <er>Hostler</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
keeper of a hostel or inn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A student in a hostel, or small unendowed college in
Oxford or Cambridge.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hostelry</ent>⟦br⟧
